      • choiceFunctionProcessor

        public boolean choiceFunctionProcessor(int functionType,
                                       int processor)
        Maybe, a function has more than one processor, Call this function to choice processor that will be process function call. The default function supports the processor type to see the function interface define.
        Parameters:
        functionType - Who will be choice processor.
        processor - Which processor will be choice.
        Returns:
        true if choice successfully, false if failed or key is not existed. UninitializedException will be thrown if function is not initialized. TypeOutOfRangeException will be thrown if type is not in pre-defined range.

        Returns:
